The household qualifies for free school meals. However, I should note that since this is an adult with no children, the practical application is moot - free school meals programs apply to school-age children. But based on the income calculation:

The household has negative income (losses) from self-employment (-$144,905), short-term capital gains (-$1,242), and long-term capital gains (-$1,862), resulting in a total income well below zero. With no positive income, this household would fall well below the federal poverty level thresholds used for free school meal eligibility (typically 130% of FPL). Therefore, the household technically qualifies (1).

