Pennsylvania does not allow net operating losses or negative income to offset taxes - but more importantly, PA taxes only income that is positive. Since all income sources are negative (losses), the taxable income in Pennsylvania is $0, resulting in $0 state income tax liability.

Pennsylvania's flat income tax rate is 3.07%, but it applies only to positive taxable income. PA does not allow losses from one income class to offset income from another, and with no positive income in any category, the tax liability is $0.

