The household is ineligible for SNAP benefits. With $190,020 in annual income ($190,000 employment + $20 interest), this far exceeds the SNAP gross income limit. For a 2-person household in 2025, the gross monthly income limit is 130% of the federal poverty level, which is approximately $2,248/month ($26,973/year). The household's monthly income of ~$15,835 is well above this threshold.

Note: While the adult is disabled (which can affect certain SNAP rules like net income tests), the gross income of $190,020 annually is so far above the limits that the household does not qualify regardless.
